collections.name: observations

properties.name: date_
properties.description: The date of the observation.

properties.name: patient
properties.description: A unique identifier for the patient.

properties.name: encounter
properties.description: A unique identifier for the medical encounter.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The code for the observation type.

properties.name: description
properties.description: The description of the observation.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The value of the observation.

properties.name: units
properties.description: The units for the observation value.

collections.description: Stores clinical observations and measurements for patients, such as body weight, height, and blood pressure.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: The columns DESCRIPTION, VALUE, and UNITS combine to form a complete fact. For example, 'Body Height' (DESCRIPTION) '166.03' (VALUE) 'cm' (UNITS).

collections.name: patients

properties.name: patient
properties.description: A unique identifier for the patient.

properties.name: birthdate
properties.description: The birth date of the patient.

properties.name: deathdate
properties.description: The death date of the patient. If null, the patient is considered to be alive.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: The age of the patient can be calculated as death year - birth year. If this field is null, it implies the patient is still alive.

properties.name: ssn
properties.description: The Social Security Number of the patient.

properties.name: drivers
properties.description: The driver's license number of the patient.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: If this field is empty or null, it implies the patient does not have a driving license.

properties.name: passport
properties.description: The passport number of the patient.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: If this field is empty or 'FALSE', it implies the patient does not have a passport.

properties.name: prefix
properties.description: The patient's name prefix (e.g., Mr., Mrs.).

properties.name: first
properties.description: The first name of the patient.

properties.name: last
properties.description: The last name of the patient.

properties.name: suffix
properties.description: The patient's name suffix (e.g., PhD, MD).

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: Suffixes like PhD, JD, MD indicate that the patient holds a doctoral degree.

properties.name: maiden
properties.description: The maiden name of the patient, if applicable.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: This field is typically applicable only to married women.

properties.name: marital
properties.description: The marital status of the patient.

properties.name: race
properties.description: The race of the patient.

properties.name: ethnicity
properties.description: The ethnicity of the patient.

properties.name: gender
properties.description: The gender of the patient.

properties.name: birthplace
properties.description: The birthplace of the patient.

properties.name: address
properties.description: The full address of the patient.

collections.description: Contains demographic and personal information for each patient.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: A patient's full name can be constructed by combining 'first' and 'last' name fields.
